# Intentional idioms used throughout this repo — silenced so the lint gate
# surfaces real problems instead of noise.
#
# SC2015 - `cond && a || b` colour-picking idiom; `a` (a var assignment) always
#          succeeds, so this is a safe ternary here.
# SC2059 - printf format strings intentionally embed escape sequences / unicode.
# SC2162 - interactive `read` prompts where backslash mangling is irrelevant.
# SC2012 - `ls` on predictable kernel/boot filenames in the Gentoo helpers.
# SC2010 - `ls | grep` on the same predictable filenames.
disable=SC2015,SC2059,SC2162,SC2012,SC2010
